The mood on campus 
was calm as students streamed out of Harvard Yard on a frigid morning 
with temperatures in the 20s. The gates around the yard were closed and 
people were allowed to leave but not enter unless they had school IDs.

A classroom building was also briefly 
evacuated Monday at the University of Massachusetts-Boston, which has 
16,000 undergraduates and graduate students who are also taking final 
exams this week.

University police got a call from someone who said they
 had seen a person with a gun in the building, which was closed while 
university, Boston and state police searched it. They determined there 
was no one with a gun and the call is being investigated, said school 
spokesman DeWayne Lehman.

